* missing 6502 instructions:
  when done, remove "unimplemented instruction" code and messages
* floppy disk support:
  - disk writing
  - read-only disks
  - other disk formats than .nib
  - function key to hot-load a floppy into a drive
* keyboard:
  - nano timer to receive ESC key
* command-line options:
  - to disable disks
  - to enable debugging
* screen modes:
  - low resolution
  - mixed low resolution/text
  - high resolution
* more hardware emulation:
  - sound
  - game paddles
